                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a05">
                    <desc>
                      ‎<locus target="#149v #153r #153v"/> (folio 149v is bound upside down): A ‎unidentified personal prayer, copied for unknown person <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ገብርኤል፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a06">
                    <desc>
                      ‎‎<locus target="#154r #154v"/>, Excerpt from Gǝ‘ǝz Grammar, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰዋስወ፡ ግእዝ፡‎ ‎ሀየል፡ መሕሳዕ፡ ዘይቤ፡ ወጠጤ። እጓለማውታ፡ ዘ፡ ድሐ። ተከዜ፡ ዘ፡ ‎‎ፈሳሽ፡ ነቅዕ፡ ዘይቤ፡ ምንጭ።...</foreign> ‎
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e01">
                      <desc>
                    words of text are written interlinearly (‎‎<locus target="#30v #‎‎44r #61v #62r #63r"/>, etc.);
                    and lines of text are written interlinearly ‎‎(‎‎<locus target="#22v #126v #132v"/>);
                    erasure markings are visible (‎‎<locus target="#20v #55r"/>);
                    text ‎has been removed (e.g., ‎‎<locus target="#56r #112r"/>)‎
                  </desc>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="e02">
                  <desc>
                    The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                    ‎Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an ‎appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate ‎script size.
                    But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe ‎completes the line of text above the end of the line (throughout)‎
                  </desc>
                </item>
